frameDefinitions: An Agent goes to an Event and is present in a relatively non-participatory way.
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.
An Importer receives Goods from an Exporting_area, across a boundary or border to a different area, the Importing_area.
This  frame covers the descriptions of tastes and smells, and has one main frame element, Source.
The word(s) in this frame detail a particular moment in time.
An object Theme moves in the direction of a Goal.
frameExamples: The Angolan guerrillas will <t>attend</t> a September meeting in Zaire.
I ca n't remember how many times he <t>visited</t> ! DNI
The U.S. <t>imported</t> some wheat in the period, although it exported about ten times as much.
Some students <t>arrived</t> at the school on Sunday.
listRoleDefinitions: The  <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who chooses to make himself present at the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Event</fen> is the deliberate set of happenings given at a particular time and place.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> attends the <fen>Event</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> attends the <fen>Event</fen>.
The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The physical entity that is permanently associated with entities or characteristics that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to use for some <fen>Purpose</fen>.  During the visit, the <fen>Agent</fen> matches location with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which a visit is made.
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that brings the <fen>Goods</fen> into the <fen>Importing_area</fen>.
The items of value whose location is changing.
The role <fen>Importing_area</fen> is the place that the <fen>Goods</fen> end up as a result of motion.
The place where the <fen>Goods</fen> are initially, before the being moved.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Importer</fen> moves the <fen>Goods</fen>.
<fen>Perceptual_source</fen> is used for the entity that is being described. A recipe can stand in for a <fen>Perceptual_source</fen> which is a kind of food.
<fen>Sensory_attribute</fen> is used for words that describe the perception itself.

The particular, salient point in time. If a specified time is present, it is the focal time. Otherwise, the unit is the focal time. If there is an appositive that specifies an entity that it not necessarily larger than the target, both the unit and the specification are the FE.
<fen>Theme</fen> is the object that moves. It may be an entity that moves under its own power, but it need not be.
<fen>Goal</fen> is any expression that tells where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up, or would end up, as a result of the motion.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arriving event occurs.
listRoleExamples: The almonds had a bitter <fex> taste</fex>.
